                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On June 1, Secretary of State Dean Acheson began his testimony before the Senate
                    Armed Services and Foreign Relations Committees. He testified daily through June
                    9, with the exception of Sunday, June 3; see <hi rend="italic">Hearings</hi>,
                    pages 1667 ff. On June 2, specifically in reply to questions from Republican
                    Senator H. Alexander Smith of New Jersey, Mr. Acheson stated that a cease-fire
                    and military settlement at or near the 38th parallel in Korea would be
                    acceptable to the United Nations, and that the Chinese Communist authorities
                    would have to be dealt with on these matters; see <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>.,
                    pages 1782–1783.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
